{{Infobox river | name = Yukawa | image = [[File:Yukawa Riv.JPG|250px|Taken on May 4, 2010]] | image_caption = Yukawa flowing near Nagakura Park (Asama Volcano in the background) | river_system = [[First-class river system]] | water_system = {{ill|Shinano River|ja|信濃川|12=draft}} | river_class = [[First-class river]] | length = | source_altitude = | flow_rate = | basin_size = | source = [[Asama Volcano]] | mouth = [[Shinano River]] (Chikuma River) | route = [[Karuizawa Town]], [[Miyota Town]], [[Saku City]], Nagano Prefecture | basin = Karuizawa Town, Miyota Town, Saku City, Nagano Prefecture | map = {{Maplink2|zoom=10|frame=yes|frame-align=center|frame-width=292|frame-height=300|frame-latitude=36.27|frame-longitude=138.52 |type=line|stroke-color=#0000ff|stroke-width=3|title=Yukawa |type2=line|stroke-color2=#777777|stroke-width2=3|id2=Q734455|title2=Shinano River |text='''Blue:''' Yukawa, '''Gray:''' Shinano River (Chikuma River) }} | notes = | sources = }}
'''Yukawa''' (湯川) is a [[river]] in [[Nagano Prefecture]], flowing through [[Karuizawa Town]], [[Miyota Town]], and [[Saku City]]. It is a [[first-class river]] in the {{ill|Shinano River|ja|信濃川|12=draft}} system. During the [[Edo Period]], it was also known as Uogawa, Ōgawa, and Hanazugawa.<ref>''Nakasendō Volume 7'', Tokyo Bijutsu, September 30, 1979, p. 10.</ref>
== Geography ==
Yukawa originates near the northern part of [[Asama Volcano]] in [[Karuizawa Town]], Nagano Prefecture. It flows through notable locations like {{ill|Shiraito Falls (Nagano)|ja|白糸の滝 (長野県)|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sengataki Falls (Karuizawa)|ja|千ヶ滝 (軽井沢町)|12=draft}}, and [[Usui Pass]], joining the Chikuma River (the local name for the Shinano River) at Naruse in Saku City. In Miyota Town, the Yukawa Valley houses the [[Yukawa Dam]], a prefectural [[flood control dam]] managed by Nagano Prefecture.
== Administrative Designation ==
The river has the following designations:<ref>Cabinet Order No. 43, March 24, 1965: "Ordinance Specifying River Systems and First-Class Rivers Under Article 4, Paragraph 1 of the River Act."</ref> * River designation: First-class river (designated in [[1965]]) * Endpoints: ** Upstream: Nagakura, Karuizawa Town, Nagano Prefecture, at the Shishiiwa land plot ** Downstream: Confluence with the Shinano River * Water system designation: [[First-class water system]], Shinano River system (designated in 1965)
